title: "pip install --upgrade deeplabcut" reverts tensorflow to v2.2.0 (from previously installed v2.6.0)
body:
### Is there an existing issue for this?

- [X] I have searched the existing issues

### Bug description

Dear devs and experts,

first of all, I am not an expert in programming or using Anaconda and python software such as DLC, so maybe I am just being stupid here. 

I started using DLC a few days ago, and after some problems got it to recognize the graphics card and was able to perform a training. However, I ran into a problem that certain folders + files that should have been created after the training were not generated, so "evaluate network" was not possible. I found somewhere the recommendation to upgrade DLC via "pip install --upgrade deeplabcut" to solve issues such as this one.

This resulted in the following. Please note the parts about tensorflow. Tensorflow was gradually reverted to 2.2.0 from the 2.6.0 which I had installed and which was working. I assume this should not be? Btw: I have CUDA 11.2.2 and cudnn 8.2.1.32 installed.

I am not sure I understand why this happened. I would be grateful if somebody could explain to me, and please forgive me if the issue has resulted from my ignorance.

All the best,
Quirin
 


### Operating System

Windows 10

### DeepLabCut version

dlc version 2.2.0.1 (today upgraded using pip install --upgrade deeplabcut)

### DeepLabCut mode

multi animal

### Device type

NVIDIA Quadro T1000

### Steps To Reproduce

_No response_
